@startuml 05-split-brain-activity
skinparam dpi 300
title Problem 5 — Split-Brain Lifecycle (TopScore)

start
:single :global leaderboard singleton\n(healthy 4-node cluster);
if (network partition?) then (yes)
  fork
    partition "Partition A {pod-1,2}" {
      :keeps existing singleton;
      :accumulates scores;
    }
  fork again
    partition "Partition B {pod-3,4}" {
      :no singleton visible;
      :re-registers a new singleton;
      :accumulates scores;
    }
  end fork
  :partition heals -> nodes reconnect;
  :":global" detects name clash;
  #ffcccc:conflict resolver kills one duplicate\nits accumulated scores discarded;
  stop
else (no)
  :normal operation;
  stop
endif

legend right
  Throughout the split, every pod's local
  liveness/readiness probe passes - K8s reports
  all-green and never acts.
  Orchestrator health model != BEAM membership.
endlegend
@enduml
